, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah.","year":-759},{"id":"rec2JkknX3cvDRSCa","ref":"Isa.1.2","text":"Hear, O heavens, and give ear, O earth: for the LORD hath spoken, I have nourished and brought up children, and they have rebelled against me.","year":-759},{"id":"rec7aE942mczsmDoz","ref":"Isa.1.3","text":"The ox knoweth his owner, and the ass his master’s crib: but Israel doth not know, my people doth not consider.","year":-759},{"id":"recMKTx7Uieg5ET0n","ref":"Isa.1.4","text":"Ah sinful nation, a people laden with iniquity, a seed of evildoers, children that are corrupters: they have forsaken the LORD, they have provoked the Holy One of Israel unto anger, they are gone away backward.","year":-759},{"id":"rec99U6f9bz3KcFFK","ref":"Isa.1.5","text":"Why should ye be stricken any more? ye will revolt more and more: the whole head is sick, and the whole heart faint.","year":-759},{"id":"recuQwWBw2NOTegWo","ref":"Isa.1.6","text":"From the sole of the foot even unto the head there is no soundness in it; but wounds, and bruises, and putrifying sores: they have not been closed, neither bound up, neither mollified with ointment.","year":-759}]}
